Method Detail

getMissingReferences

public static java.util.List<ModelerDependencies.FlexfieldReference> getMissingReferences(oracle.jbo.server.DBTransaction transaction,
                                                                                          java.lang.String defFullName)
                                                                                   throws oracle.mds.core.MetadataNotFoundException
Gets the references to missing flexfields used in an ADF object if any. A flexfield is considered missing if any of its corresponding ADF objects is missing in MDS. The return list is sorted in the order defined by FlexfieldReference.

Parameters:
transaction - the DB transaction for accessing flexfield metadata
defFullName - the full name of the ADF object
Returns:
the references to missing flexfields; empty list if no references to flexfields are found or there is no missing references
Throws:
oracle.mds.core.MetadataNotFoundException - if the object of the given name or its super objects cannot be found
oracle.jbo.JboException - if an error occurred while accessing the flexfield metadata

getMdsResourceNames

public static ModelerDependencies.MdsResourceNames getMdsResourceNames()
                                                                throws java.sql.SQLException
Gets the names of all flexfield MDS resources based on the definitions from the default data source. The database connection is obtained by ApplSessionUtil.getNewConnection(). An MDS resource name is either a package name such as "/a/b/c/" or a document name such as "/o/a/xyz.xml". A package name always ends with "/".

Returns:
a collection of flexfield MDS resource names
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given connection is null
java.sql.SQLException - if an error occurs while retrieving the flexfield definitions

getMdsResourceNames

public static ModelerDependencies.MdsResourceNames getMdsResourceNames(java.sql.Connection connection)
                                                                throws java.sql.SQLException
Gets the names of all flexfield MDS resources. An MDS resource name is either a package name such as "/a/b/c/" or a document name such as "/o/a/xyz.xml". A package name always ends with "/".

Parameters:
connection - the JDBC connection to the database that provides the flexfield definitions.
Returns:
a collection of flexfield MDS resource names
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given connection is null
java.sql.SQLException - if an error occurs while retrieving the flexfield definitions
